## 2. Component Library

### Location
Components are in `src/components/`:
- `Button.jsx` - Primary button component with variants
- `IconDot.jsx`, `IconOpen.jsx`, `IconCross.jsx` - Icon components
- `IconVolumeOn.jsx`, `IconVolumeOff.jsx` - Audio control icons

### Export Pattern
All components are exported via barrel file `src/components/index.js`:

```javascript
export { default as Button } from './Button';
export { default as IconDot } from './IconDot';
// ... etc
```

### Button Component API

```jsx
<Button 
  variant="black"    // "black" | "white" | "gray"
  href="/link"       // Optional - renders as <a> if provided
  icon={<IconOpen />} // Optional - icon displayed after text
  className=""       // Additional classes
>
  Button Text
</Button>
```

**Button Variants:**
- `black` - `bg-brand-black text-brand-white` (primary)
- `white` - `bg-brand-white text-brand-black` (on dark backgrounds)
- `gray` - `bg-gray-20 text-brand-black` (secondary)

### Squircle Implementation
The project uses `@squircle-js/react` for iOS-style smooth corners:

```jsx
import { Squircle } from '@squircle-js/react';

<Squircle 
  cornerRadius={9999}     // Capsule for buttons
  cornerSmoothing={1}     // Maximum smoothing
  className="..."
>
  Content
</Squircle>
```

CSS class `.squircle` is also available for native corner-shape support.

