## 9. Figma to Code Guidelines

### When Implementing Figma Designs:

1. **Colors**: Always use Tailwind token classes (`text-brand-black`, `bg-gray-10`)
2. **Typography**: Use predefined font sizes (`text-h1`, `text-button`, `text-label`)
3. **Buttons**: Use the `<Button>` component with appropriate variant
4. **Icons**: Create new icons following the `Icon*.jsx` pattern
5. **Spacing**: Use Tailwind spacing utilities; match Figma values with closest Tailwind class
6. **Border Radius**: Use `rounded-card` (56px), `rounded-image` (42px), or `rounded-full`
7. **Smooth Corners**: Apply `.squircle` class or use `<Squircle>` component

### Component Creation Checklist:
- [ ] Export from barrel file (`components/index.js` or `sections/index.js`)
- [ ] Accept `className` prop for composition
- [ ] Use design tokens from Tailwind config
- [ ] Include `will-change-transform` for animated elements
- [ ] Follow existing naming conventions



